	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (name entire): qui scriba fuerat, dictator sine mag. eq. coactus abdicare. A lowborn subordinate of the Consul. He abdicated but kept his insignia (Liv. Per. 19; Suet. Tib. 2, ilycian viatorem, codd.; Degrassi 42f., 116, 436f.)." .
